-- Corp. GEO Seeks License to Operate as Bank, El Economista Says
-- B y   A d r i a n a   L o p e z   C a r a v e o
-- 2012-03-08T19:48:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/corp-geo-seeks-license-to-operate-as-bank-el-economista-says.html
Corporacion GEO (GEOB)  SAB,  Mexico ’s
second-largest homebuilder by sales, is seeking a banking
license for its lending unit, newspaper  El Economista  reported
today.  The company’s Equipate unit will seek a license from
Mexican regulators next year, the Mexico City-based newspaper
reported, citing an interview with Geo Chief Executive Officer
Luis Orvananos.  The homebuilder plans to invest 200 million pesos ($15.7
million) on the project and may seek to partner with a financial
company, according to El Economista.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adriana Lopez Caraveo in Mexico City at 
 adrianalopez@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
